1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:03,000
When you went to the bathroom

2
00:00:03,375 --> 00:00:05,041
It was outside prayer times

3
00:00:06,375 --> 00:00:08,625
You would knock on
the door for the guard

4
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:11,250
And tell him you want to go to
the bathroom so he opens the door

5
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:14,625
During prayer times,
it got a little crowded

6
00:00:14,666 --> 00:00:16,375
You had to be quick

7
00:00:17,375 --> 00:00:21,166
So you did not delay those behind you from
praying, because they would be punished

8
00:00:21,916 --> 00:00:23,666
Especially during
the dawn prayer

9
00:00:23,750 --> 00:00:26,500
You had to be ready, and he would
wake you up an hour before prayer

10
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:29,375
Until you finished ablution

11
00:00:30,250 --> 00:00:31,375
And went down to prayer

12
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:33,916
Interviewer: How was
the water? Witness: Cold

13
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,666
Interviewer: Was there soap or
cleaning supplies? Witness: Yes, soap
